173
00:17:57.660 --> 00:18:00.504
However it got here.
however it germinated here.

174
00:18:00.621 --> 00:18:04.000
once it got here.
it spread very quickly.

175
00:18:21.684 --> 00:18:25.063
I remember I was in high school

176
00:18:26.022 --> 00:18:30.302
and we heard this song. "I wonder
how many times you've had sex?"

177
00:18:30.401 --> 00:18:32.975
And at that time South Africa
was very conservative.

178
00:18:33.070 --> 00:18:35.414
It was the height of apartheid.

179
00:18:36.157 --> 00:18:38.310
and there wasn't television here.

180
00:18:38.409 --> 00:18:41.813
That's how conservative it was.
'cause television was communist.

181
00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:44.665
It was really... You wouldn't believe.

182
00:18:45.875 --> 00:18:47.718
Everything was restricted.
everything was censored.

183
00:18:47.835 --> 00:18:49.157
Everything was...

184
00:18:49.253 --> 00:18:51.426
And here's this guy singing this song.

185
00:18:51.547 --> 00:18:54.166
<i>"Who's that?" Said. "That's Rodriguez."</i>

186
00:18:54.258 --> 00:18:58.559
<i>And he became something
of a rebel son' of icon.</i>

187
00:18:59.055 --> 00:19:01.774
<i>But the strange thing was
that we all bought his records.</i>

188
00:19:01.849 --> 00:19:04.728
<i>Everybody I knew had his records.
I Wonder.</i>

189
00:19:05.394 --> 00:19:06.967
that was the big song
that everybody was singing

190
00:19:07.063 --> 00:19:08.510
and we all bought a record.

191
00:19:08.606 --> 00:19:12.281
And there he was on the cover.
sort of a hippy with shades.

192
00:19:12.401 --> 00:19:15.475
But nobody knew anything about him.
He was a mystery.

193
00:19:15.571 --> 00:19:19.451
Unlike other artists
that you could read about from America.

194
00:19:19.575 --> 00:19:24.026
get to know something about them.
there was zilch. Nobody knew anything.

195
