"Do you wanna do it?"
I said. "Of course we wanna do it."

881
01:04:48.426 --> 01:04:51.475
"Why? Where is he?"
"Now they found him.

882
01:04:51.596 --> 01:04:55.146
"They found him. he's alive. he's gonna
come and tour in South Africa."

883
01:04:55.241 --> 01:04:59.317
"Are we gonna be the opening band?"
So I couldn't really believe this.

884
01:05:00.814 --> 01:05:05.390
And then I got all the information:
he's living in Detroit and everything.

885
01:05:05.485 --> 01:05:07.203
And then a little while later he said.

886
01:05:07.295 --> 01:05:09.823
"Look. it turns out
he hasn't got a band.

887
01:05:09.948 --> 01:05:13.498
"Could we be the support band?"
I mean his band.

888
01:05:14.452 --> 01:05:18.002
I remember. even then. we were sort of.

889
01:05:19.499 --> 01:05:21.376
"Is this really gonna be Rodriguez?"

890
01:05:21.476 --> 01:05:24.004
We'll only know
if he can actually sing these songs.

891
01:05:24.129 --> 01:05:27.383
I mean. we don't know.
What if it's just some guy?

892
01:05:27.882 --> 01:05:29.008
<i>It was just like</i>

893
01:05:29.134 --> 01:05:30.351
<i>one day we heard about it</i>

894
01:05:30.443 --> 01:05:32.641
<i>and the next day we were there.</i>

895
01:05:34.013 --> 01:05:35.856
<i>trying to believe our eyes.</i>

896
01:05:35.974 --> 01:05:38.853
<i>thinking it was just all very shocking.</i>

897
01:05:38.977 --> 01:05:41.196
<i>I don't know. he took to it really easy.</i>

898
01:05:41.287 --> 01:05:43.565
<i>He just walked in and did his thing</i>

899
01:05:43.665 --> 01:05:47.195
<i>and I was amazed that he did so well.</i>

900
01:05:47.293 --> 01:05:48.194
<i>But he's not all</i>

901
01:05:48.319 --> 01:05:49.366
<i>"head in the clouds" kinda guy.</i>

902
01:05:49.487 --> 01:05:53.208
<i>He's a little bit too much grounded.</i>

903
01:05:53.283 --> 01:05:54.910
<i>He didn't take advantage</i>

904
01:05:55.009 --> 01:05:57.037
<i>of all the amenities and stuff.</i>

905
01:05:57.120 --> 01:05:59.919
He didn't sleep in the big
double king size bed.

906
01:06:00.014 --> 01:06:03.760
He kinda curled up on the love seat
and I found him there and...

907
01:06:03.851 --> 01:06:07.255
Yeah. he just didn't think somebody
should have to make another bed

908
01:06:07.355 --> 01:06:09.257
because he messed it up or...

909
01:06:09.357 --> 01:06:10.634
<i>There was a time</i>

910
01:06:10.717 --> 01:06:12.765
<i>where I stayed in the house we were at</i>

911
01:06:12.886 --> 01:06:15.389
<i>and everyone else had gone out.</i>

912
01:06:15.472 --> 01:06:17.099
<i>The phone rang and it kept ringing.</i>

913
01:06:17.223 --> 01:06:19.317
<i>so I decided to answer it.</i>

914
01:06:19.392 --> 01:06:20.769
And it was a reporter

915
01:06:20.894 --> 01:06:22.737
looking to speak with Rodriguez

916
01:06:22.812 --> 01:06:25.782
and set up time for an interview.

917
01:06:26.483 --> 01:06:31.184
And then. before she hung up.
after I told her to call back later

918
01:06:31.279 --> 01:06:33.657
to talk to someone
'cause I couldn't help her.

919
01:06:33.740 --> 01:06:38.337
she told me that she wanted to know.
between she and I.

920
01:06:38.411 --> 01:06:40.334
if it was the real Rodriguez.

921
01:06:42.999 --> 01:06:45.297
We were rehearsing with a CD

922
01:06:45.393 --> 01:06:47.412
of the songs that we've got

923
01:06:47.504 --> 01:06:48.926
in the studio here in Cape Town

924
01:06:49.005 --> 01:06:52.375
on the day that he came
from the airport. when he arrived.

925
01:06:52.467 --> 01:06:56.042
and we were actually in the middle
of a song when he walked in

926
01:06:56.262 --> 01:06:58.936
and just took over the microphone
and finished the song.

927
01:06:59.015 --> 01:07:01.484
We switched off the CD player

928
01:07:01.576 --> 01:07:04.320
and it was. like. completely seamless.

929
01:07:04.412 --> 01:07:05.689
<i>Completely seamless.</i>

930
01:07:05.772 --> 01:07:07.945
<i>I mean. "OK. this is the guy."</i>

931
01:07:08.024 --> 01:07:09.822
<i>I think we all knew this is</i>

932
01:07:09.917 --> 01:07:11.945
<i>gonna be something really special.</i>

933
01:07:29.963 --> 01:07:32.637
<i>Thank you. Cape Town. Thank you.</i>

934
01:07:34.509 --> 01:07:35.556
<i>When we. uh...</i>

935
01:07:35.635 --> 01:07:36.727
<i>initially got on a plane.</i>

936
01:07:36.803 --> 01:07:38.751
<i>I thought maybe there 'd be. hopefully.</i>

937
01:07:38.846 --> 01:07:40.965
<i>20 people in the audience.</i>

938
01:07:41.516 --> 01:07:42.893
Hopefully.

939
01:07:44.185 --> 01:07:47.064
But it turned out really.
really different than that.

940
01:07:47.188 --> 01:07:49.987
And there's old people and young people

941
01:07:50.066 --> 01:07:53.161
and they're coming to see the show.

942
01:07:53.236 --> 01:07:57.241
<i>And there's my step-dad on the stage...
Before he went on stage.</i>

943
01:07:57.323 --> 01:07:59.417
<i>'cause I wanted to take
a picture of the audience.</i>

944
01:07:59.492 --> 01:08:01.494
<i>since nobody's gonna believe this.</i>

945
01:08:01.578 --> 01:08:03.046
<i>You must remember. this guy.</i>

946
01:08:03.137 --> 01:08:06.086
<i>it's like seeing someone like Elvis
come back from the dead.</i>

947
01:08:06.207 --> 01:08:07.675
<i>People in the audience
still don't believe it.</i>

948
01:08:07.750 --> 01:08:09.593
<i>They're standing there.
They're at the concert.</i>

949
01:08:09.669 --> 01:08:11.262
They've paid their money.

950
01:08:11.337 --> 01:08:13.055
They still don't believe that Rodriguez

951
01:08:13.147 --> 01:08:15.049
is actually gonna walk on that stage.

952
01:08:41.909 --> 01:08:45.630
<i>Are you ready?</i>

953
01:08:47.040 --> 01:08:48.587
<i>Please welcome...</i>

954
01:08:49.375 --> 01:08:50.718
<i>Rodriguez!</i>

955
01:09:29.123 --> 01:09:31.091
<i>It was almost as if he
didn't even have to play.</i>

956
01:09:31.167 --> 01:09:33.295
<i>They were just happy to see him.</i>

957
01:09:33.378 --> 01:09:34.595
<i>So. for a time.</i>

958
01:09:34.671 --> 01:09:37.641
<i>I think they wanted to meet.</i>

959
01:09:38.508 --> 01:09:39.885
<i>It was a reunion.</i>

960
01:09:41.052 --> 01:09:42.975
<i>It was something
completely different.</i>

961
01:09:43.054 --> 01:09:45.182
<i>It was for everybody there. I'm sure.</i>

962
01:09:45.306 --> 01:09:49.106
<i>the most exciting concert they'd
ever been to. Because it was unique.</i>

963
01:09:49.185 --> 01:09:50.732
<i>We'd never seen Rodriguez.</i>

964
01:09:50.812 --> 01:09:51.813
<i>And all you heard</i>

965
01:09:51.896 --> 01:09:54.069
<i>was the bass player just playing...</i>

966
01:09:58.653 --> 01:10:00.845
<i>And Rodriguez wandered out
to the front of the stage</i>

967
01:10:00.947 --> 01:10:01.948
<i>and the bass player</i>

968
01:10:02.031 --> 01:10:03.032
<i>actually just stopped playing.</i>

969
01:10:03.116 --> 01:10:04.163
<i>And it took a while.</i>

970
01:10:04.242 --> 01:10:05.585
<i>There was about five or ten minutes</i>

971
01:10:05.660 --> 01:10:08.539
<i>of just people screaming at him.</i>

972
01:10:30.518 --> 01:10:32.987
<i>Thanks for keeping me alive.</i>

973
01:11:31.913 --> 01:11:33.540
<i>I think to go</i>

974
01:11:33.623 --> 01:11:35.796
from being the outcast

975
01:11:35.875 --> 01:11:40.247
to being. uh. who he really was.

976
01:11:40.838 --> 01:11:46.265
Because it was as though it was him
again... and that was who he was.

977
01:11:46.344 --> 01:11:49.769
a musician on stage.
playing for his fans.

978
01:12:11.536 --> 01:12:14.710
<i>I thought I would see him
being bewildered</i>

979
01:12:14.789 --> 01:12:17.292
<i>at all these people staring up at him.</i>

980
01:12:17.375 --> 01:12:20.745
<i>I saw the opposite.
I saw this absolute tranquility.</i>

981
01:12:20.837 --> 01:12:24.512
<i>There was absolute serenity on his face.
Total.</i>

982
01:12:24.924 --> 01:12:28.749
<i>It's like he had arrived at that thing.
at that place</i>

983
01:12:28.845 --> 01:12:31.223
<i>he'd tried to find his whole life.</i>

984
01:12:31.305 --> 01:12:33.649
<i>Home is acceptance.</i>

985
01:12:34.058 --> 01:12:37.562
<i>Here's a guy who'd lived somewhere else.
on the other side of the earth.</i>

986
01:12:37.645 --> 01:12:40.799
<i>and it was almost as if
he had found his home.</i>

987
01:12:40.898 --> 01:12:42.900
<i>And I looked around at all these people</i>

988
01:12:42.984 --> 01:12:46.659
<i>and I thought. "This is
a once-in-a-lifetime experience.</i>

989
01:12:46.737 --> 01:12:49.786
<i>"This is never going to happen again."</i>

990
01:13:40.416 --> 01:13:42.919
<i>Well. isn't this all
our great fate?</i>

991
01:13:43.019 --> 01:13:47.346
Your dreams of yourself. the higher
forms of yourself is that one day

992
01:13:47.924 --> 01:13:52.475
you will be recognised and that
your talents and everything else.

993
01:13:53.429 --> 01:13:56.023
will suddenly become visible
to the world.

994
01:13:56.098 --> 01:14:00.604
I mean. most of us die
without coming anywhere close

995
01:14:00.686 --> 01:14:03.781
to that sort of magic.

996
01:14:03.856 --> 01:14:05.233
<i>I tried to get him to talk about that</i>

997
01:14:05.316 --> 01:14:06.613
<i>when I interviewed him.</i>

998
01:14:06.692 --> 01:14:08.114
<i>about how strange it was.</i>

999
01:14:08.194 --> 01:14:10.413
<i>and I got absolutely nothing back.</i>

1000
01:14:10.488 --> 01:14:12.081
<i>Absolutely nothing back.</i>

1001
01:14:12.156 --> 01:14:13.373
<i>And I couldn't tell whether</i>

1002
01:14:13.449 --> 01:14:15.622
<i>he was just like son' of cripplingly shy</i>

1003
01:14:15.701 --> 01:14:16.827
<i>or whether I was</i>

1004
01:14:16.911 --> 01:14:18.037
<i>asking the wrong questions</i>

1005
01:14:18.120 --> 01:14:19.167
<i>or there was a language barrier</i>

1006
01:14:19.246 --> 01:14:20.463
<i>or whatever. He just...</i>

1007
01:14:20.581 --> 01:14:25.587
Maybe that was OK as well
because he preserved his mystery.

1008
01:14:25.670 --> 01:14:27.718
I walked away
from that interview saying.

1009
01:14:28.005 --> 01:14:30.679
"This is all too strange to be true."

1010
01:14:30.758 --> 01:14:33.386
<i>It remains too strange to be true.</i>

1011
01:14:33.469 --> 01:14:34.721
<i>"These are the days</i>

1012
01:14:34.804 --> 01:14:36.351
<i>"of miracles and wonder."</i>

1013
01:14:58.869 --> 01:15:01.122
<i>Oh. they were so sweet.</i>

1014
01:15:01.205 --> 01:15:03.378
<i>I didn't believe it.</i>

1015
01:15:03.457 --> 01:15:06.210
<i>And I still don't. but the thing is...</i>

1016
01:15:06.293 --> 01:15:11.516
So when I went on stage
5.000 seats all set up.

1017
01:15:12.008 --> 01:15:14.352
white seats. and the thing is...

1018
01:15:14.677 --> 01:15:17.271
And I said. "This is..."

1019
01:15:18.556 --> 01:15:23.187
<i>So when I played a show. they jumped
out of their seats and rushed the stage.</i>

1020
01:15:24.895 --> 01:15:29.071
<i>South Africa made me feel like
more than a prince.</i>

1021
01:15:29.734 --> 01:15:32.979
<i>And then signing the autographs
for. like. a couple of hours.</i>

1022
01:15:33.070 --> 01:15:37.291
<i>I mean. just the line of people
bringing their guitars to be signed.</i>

1023
01:15:37.366 --> 01:15:39.414
<i>bringing their CDs and...</i>

1024
01:15:39.493 --> 01:15:40.961
<i>The most amazing thing I'd seen</i>

1025
01:15:41.037 --> 01:15:43.916
<i>was the man with his tattoo
of the Cold Fact.</i>

1026
01:15:43.998 --> 01:15:48.028
<i>He was a Rodriguez impersonator.
That just stoked my fire.</i>

1027
01:15:48.127 --> 01:15:51.222
<i>I was like.
"Man. that is just too crazy."</i>

1028
01:15:54.091 --> 01:15:56.310
I have with me here.
presented to Rodriguez

1029
01:15:56.385 --> 01:15:58.308
<i>for sales of the album Cold Fact.</i>

1030
01:16:04.268 --> 01:16:06.145
Now just tell the States that.
OK. will you?

1031
01:16:07.730 --> 01:16:11.885
American singer Rodriguez
is certainly alive and well

1032
01:16:11.984 --> 01:16:14.328
and with us in the Front Row tonight.
Welcome.

1033
01:16:14.445 --> 01:16:15.913
Very kind. How are you?

1034
01:16:15.988 --> 01:16:18.912
I've heard some really riveting tales
about your "death."

1035
01:16:18.991 --> 01:16:21.995
I mean. they range from you pouring
petrol all over yourself on stage

1036
01:16:22.078 --> 01:16:27.084
and committing suicide to taking
a drug overdose and dying in prison.

1037
01:16:37.259 --> 01:16:42.982
<i>Yeah. it was a beautiful.
beautiful dream</i>

1038
01:16:44.975 --> 01:16:47.694
<i>and then you gotta go back.</i>

1039
01:16:47.812 --> 01:16:50.440
My dad said he's got two lives.

1040
01:16:51.524 --> 01:16:55.700
The carriage turns into the pumpkin bus
or something. It's like...

1041
01:16:55.820 --> 01:16:58.198
<i>Did people in Detroit believe you</i>

1042
01:16:58.280 --> 01:17:01.275
when you came back
and told them what had happened?

1043
01:17:01.367 --> 01:17:05.497
You know. people in Detroit
need to hear something good.

1044
01:17:06.330 --> 01:17:08.278
<i>I'm not sure how much of it
they believed</i>

1045
01:17:08.374 --> 01:17:10.877
<i>because it is a grandiose story.</i>

1046
01:17:12.044 --> 01:17:13.637
It sounds like something
you would make up

1047
01:17:13.712 --> 01:17:16.966
if you were bragging on some dream
or something.

1048
01:17:18.050 --> 01:17:20.473
<i>He was really quite famous.</i>

1049
01:17:20.553 --> 01:17:23.227
<i>He'd be. you know.
tearing down this old shack</i>

1050
01:17:23.305 --> 01:17:26.800
<i>or he'd be sweeping up filth or dirt</i>

1051
01:17:26.892 --> 01:17:30.066
<i>and he started to show me one day.
and I didn't believe him.</i>

1052
01:17:30.146 --> 01:17:33.992
<i>about the album
and how it got to be so popular.</i>

1053
01:17:34.066 --> 01:17:35.739
Somebody had a bootleg copy
of this thing

1054
01:17:35.860 --> 01:17:37.908
and it spread around and everyone...

1055
01:17:37.987 --> 01:17:42.663
It got to be so popular
that children could recite it

1056
01:17:42.741 --> 01:17:47.087
and sing the song word for word...
all of the songs word for word.

1057
01:17:47.163 --> 01:17:50.588
And I had never heard of the album
and I said. "Can you get me an album?"

1058
01:17:50.666 --> 01:17:52.088
And he couldn't even get me one.

1059
01:17:52.168 --> 01:17:55.012
I mean. that's how
obscure of a thing it was.

1060
01:17:55.087 --> 01:17:59.893
But he had all these photos and stuff.
with these giant crowds.

1061
01:18:00.092 --> 01:18:03.096
20.000 people.
like Woodstock or something.

1062
01:18:03.179 --> 01:18:04.772
Like. "Are you kidding me? That's you?"

1063
01:18:06.098 --> 01:18:09.102
<i>I thought it was Photoshopped
or something. I didn't believe him.</i>

1064
01:18:09.185 --> 01:18:12.860
<i>But he had all these giant crowds
and he was quite content</i>

1065
01:18:12.938 --> 01:18:16.513
<i>to just go and sweep up people's lawns</i>

1066
01:18:16.609 --> 01:18:20.614
<i>or clean up and do manual labor.
He stayed.</i>

1067
01:18:21.614 --> 01:18:27.121
He lives a very. very. very modest life.

1068
01:18:29.038 --> 01:18:30.415
<i>Definitely.</i>

1069
01:18:31.123 --> 01:18:33.296
<i>There's definitely no excess.</i>

1070
01:18:34.752 --> 01:18:39.883
<i>and he definitely still works hard
in order to make ends meet.</i>

1071
01:18:40.591 --> 01:18:46.173
<i>And there's no glamour to his life
in that sense.</i>

1072
01:18:46.472 --> 01:18:49.046
<i>But he must be a rich man today?</i>

1073
01:18:49.141 --> 01:18:51.314
<i>No.</i>

1074
01:18:51.393 --> 01:18:55.318
<i>Rich in a lot of things
but perhaps not material things.</i>

1075
01:18:55.397 --> 01:18:57.741
<i>I guess it just never got to that.</i>

1076
01:18:57.816 --> 01:18:59.409
<i>But he's sold
hundreds of thousands of records</i>

1077
01:18:59.485 --> 01:19:00.987
<i>in South Africa.</i>

1078
01:19:01.086 --> 01:19:02.508
Well. yes.

1079
01:19:03.489 --> 01:19:07.289
But I believe there's a great deal
of perhaps bootlegging.

1080
01:19:08.494 --> 01:19:11.714
piracy. such like that. Perhaps...

1081
01:19:12.957 --> 01:19:15.176
Perhaps other people are rich.

1082
01:20:16.186 --> 01:20:17.779
<i>You know.
when I think about that night</i>

1083
01:20:17.871 --> 01:20:19.739
<i>when I spoke to Eva on the telephone.</i>

1084
01:20:20.441 --> 01:20:23.515
<i>we could not have imagined
how much our lives were gonna change</i>

1085
01:20:23.610 --> 01:20:25.283
<i>after that phone call.</i>

1086
01:20:25.379 --> 01:20:27.281
<i>Eva came on tour with Rodriguez</i>

1087
01:20:27.406 --> 01:20:29.980
<i>and the organizers arranged
a chaperone bodyguard</i>

1088
01:20:30.075 --> 01:20:32.524
<i>to drive them around
and they fell in love.</i>

1089
01:20:32.619 --> 01:20:34.121
<i>And they have a child.</i>

1090
01:20:34.246 --> 01:20:38.797
<i>So Rodriguez has a South African
grandson. a South African grandchild.</i>

1091
01:20:38.917 --> 01:20:42.196
<i>For me. I used to be a jeweler
in Johannesburg.</i>

1092
01:20:42.296 --> 01:20:44.665
<i>I now live in Cape Town
and have a music store.</i>

1093
01:20:44.757 --> 01:20:47.761
<i>Things changed so much for us.</i>

1094
01:20:47.885 --> 01:20:50.163
<i>But. except for one person.
and that's Rodriguez.</i>

1095
01:20:50.262 --> 01:20:52.381
<i>For him. nothing has changed.</i>

1096
01:20:52.473 --> 01:20:56.003
<i>The life that he was living
is still the life that he's living now.</i>

1097
01:20:56.101 --> 01:21:00.222
<i>What he's demonstrated
very clearly is that you have a choice.</i>

1098
01:21:00.314 --> 01:21:03.388
<i>He took all that torment.
all that agony.</i>

1099
01:21:03.484 --> 01:21:05.512
<i>all that confusion and pain.</i>

1100
01:21:05.611 --> 01:21:08.310
<i>and he transformed it
into something beautiful.</i>

1101
01:21:09.114 --> 01:21:11.287
He's like the silk worm. you know?

1102
01:21:11.383 --> 01:21:16.360
You take this raw material
and you transform it.

1103
01:21:16.580 --> 01:21:19.959
